final introductionHTML = '<p>Techkriti is the hub for innovation and excellence in the field of Science and technology for the inquisitive young minds in India. Ever since its inception in 1995, it has been a trademark for excellence, a platform for many to learn, showcase and innovate. Over the years, during our 25-year long journey, Techkriti has evolved to be the grandest of all. Known as Asia’s largest technical and entrepreneurial festival, Techkriti‘s ever increasing enthusiastic crowd, with distinguished guests of honour in the fields of Technology, innovation and entrepreneurship with world-class tech at display makes the festival even more splendour. With such repute at stake hospitality of our guests is premier to us.</p>\n<p>The Hospitality team serves to cater the needs and requirements of one and all. We make sure your stay in campus is holistic and comfortable, ensuring best accommodation for everyone is our prime aim. Simultaneously your gastronomic urges are also taken care of by the canteens and food courts serving food all day long. We constantly strive to make your experience a memorable one.</p>\n<p>Hope to see you in Techkriti 2019, to witness the technopreneurial matrix that we were forging throughout our 25-year journey.</p>';

final contactHTML = '<p>For any queries contact any of the following people or mail us at <a href="mailto:hospitality@techkriti.org">hospitality@techkriti.org</a></p>\n<p>Namit Garg - 7318019009</p>\n<p>Akashdeep Singh - 7275436461</p>\n<p>Devendra Kumar Neel - 9929937399</p>\n<p>Sarvesh Chaudhary - 7380518190</p>';

final faqHTML = '<ul>\n<li>\n<p>We are a group of friends not participating in any of the major competitions and just coming to Techkriti to have fun. Would we be allowed?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No, you can come to Techkriti only if you participate in one of the events or workshops.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>I have the payment receipt, what should I do next to avail accommodation?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No further step is required; just present the hard copy of the receipt when you report to the hospitality desk. The registration fee(Rs .1800) plus the security deposit (Rs. 200) is to be paid before you arrive at the campus for the festival (7th-10th March), mode of payment being online.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>What is the procedure to be followed after we reach IIT Kanpur?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>You need to report to the Hospitality Desk behind OAT(New- SAC) along with your college identity card.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You will have to produce the receipt of your online payment and a recent passport size photograph.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In case of a big contingent, the contingent leader needs to present the ID cards of all the people in his contingent at the hospitality desk along with a list of all the people. Accommodation would be strictly on a shared basis.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>My parents or professors want to accompany me, is this allowed?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No, only the confirmed participants are allowed to enter the institute premises.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Can two participants be from different colleges in a team event?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Yes, Techkriti does not restrict cross participation from colleges in a team event.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Can I get accommodation on 5th March or before, although the festival starts from 7th of March?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No, accommodation will be provided from the evening of 6th March. All the participants coming before can stay in hotels outside IIT Kanpur.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>';

final feeHTML = '<p><strong>Accommodation Fees:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Accommodation fees will be Rs. 2000 (inclusive of all taxes and security deposit of Rs. 200) for an individual participant. Get an exclusive Techkriti T-shirt with an additional payment of just Rs.100 (only for the first 500 participants).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Mattresses and pillows will be provided to all the participants who have confirmed accommodation. You need not to stuff your backpacks with the same. However, participants need to bring their own blankets.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Food is not included in the accommodation fees which each individual has to manage via coupons/cash in the mess or canteen available in their respective Hall of Residence.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Accommodation Fees includes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Accommodation facility</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Entry Passes to all Concerts, Shows and Talks</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Participation in any number of competitions</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accommodation Fee doesn’t include the workshop fee. The hospitality fee is compulsory for all the participants.</p>\n<p><strong>For Workshop participants:</strong> The accommodation fee is mandatory for all the participants.</p>\n<p><strong>For Competitions participants:</strong> The accommodation fee is mandatory for all the participants.</p>\n<p><strong>Check-in &amp; Check-out details:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Check-in: 6th March 2019, 5 PM onwards</li>\n<li>Check-out: 11th March 2019, till 10 AM (please note this is the last day for checkout)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Please note that accommodation will not be provided before the above-mentioned check-in date and time.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Security Deposit Policy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Security Deposit of Rs. 200 will only be refundable if the participant returns his/her respective HOSPITALITY Booklet back at the Hospitality Desk before 10 AM, 11th March 2019.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Refund Procedure will be online and the money will be refunded after the end of the festival within 30 working days. Refund would be processed to the same account from which the payment was made.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In case any damage was done to the property or things of Techkriti’19/Institute the money will be deducted from the responsible participant’s security deposit.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Refund Policy for Cancellation:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>All the refund requests have to be filled <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/ttsGeaWlED2bvWQ83">here</a>. No refund requests received over mail will be entertained.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>50% cashback for all requests received till 15th February 2019.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>20% cashback for all requests received till 22nd February 2019.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>No refund requests will be entertained after the specified dates.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>';

final instructionsHTML = '<ul><li><p>All the participants are advised to bring all the materials required for the event until unless Techkriti ensures to provide them to you.</p></li><li><p>Techkriti team will not be responsible for any event clashes. Hence, it is advised to not participate in more than 2 events.</p></li><li><p>Hospitality booklet provided to you after registration will act as your identity card in the campus. It will also act as a pass for all talks and shows.</p></li><li><p>All the participants are requested to be punctual while attending any Event/Talk/Show as no excuse will be entertained for the delay.</p></li><li><p>Every participant is individually/solely responsible for his/her own belongings.</p></li><li><p>It would be good if each and every participant cooperates with Techkriti Organising Team and SIS Guards regarding formalities.</p></li><li><p>If any miscommunication arises, please be patient and polite. Techkriti Team will provide assistance in resolving it immediately.</p></li><li><p>To be safe in the campus all the participants are requested to follow the Hospitality and Security guidelines with no violation.</p></li><li><p>As Techkriti will not provide blankets, participants are strictly advised to bring their own as the weather gets cold during the night in Kanpur.</p></li><li><p>As the parking space available within the IITK premises is very less, no permission will be entertained to accommodate the personal vehicle of the participant.</p></li><li><p>Consumption of Alcohol, Cigarettes or any kind of Intoxicant within the IITK premises is strictly prohibited.</p></li><li><p>Entering into restricted areas, not maintaining cleanliness as well as silence in campus areas would not be tolerated.</p></li><li><p>Damaging Institute property and Gender Sensitivity issues will be taken very seriously.</p></li><li><p>In the event of any untoward incident or misbehaviour of any kind, Techkriti team reserves the right to take any punitive action as deemed necessary, even to the extent of confiscating the security deposit and registration fees, cancelling the participation of the concerned college, escorting them off the campus and sending a report of misconduct to the head of concerned institution.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Note:</strong> The above points are the outline of the code of conduct. Detailed guidelines will be mentioned later.</p>';

final reachingHTML = '<p>Reaching IIT Kanpur is fairly easy and hassle-free. The main modes of travel are cabs and auto rickshaws which are fairly cheap and frequent.</p><p><strong>From Kanpur Central Railway Station to IITK Campus:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepaid Taxis and autos are easily available. It is preferred to exit through PF no. 9 of the Railway Station as the auto stand is adjacent to it.</p></li><li><p>Rates: Rs. 350 for a taxi (for convenience, it’s better to book ola/uber cab) and Rs. 250 for an auto.</p></li><li><p>Shared autos can also be availed at a cheaper cost which may include break journey so please confirm the dropping point (IIT Kanpur gate) beforehand.</p></li><li><p>Scheduled buses are regularly operated by IITK bus service, which is available outside Platform no.1 and the timing of IITK buses is as follows: <a href="https://www.iitk.ac.in/new/bus-service">Bus Schedule</a></p></li></ul><p><strong>From Kanpur Interstate Bus Stand (Jhakarkati) to IITK Campus:</strong></p><ul><li><p>You can board a bus from here that drops you off at the main gate of IIT Kanpur which is 1km from the campus centre.</p></li><li><p>You can also avail autos from here and the rates are Rs. 200 appx. (for convenience, it’s better to book ola/uber cab)</p></li><li><p>Shared autos can also be availed at a cheaper cost which may include break journey so please confirm the dropping point (IIT Kanpur gate) beforehand.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Note:</strong> All the participants are required to directly report at the Hospitality desk in Events Ground (behind the New SAC) as soon as they arrive at the campus for accommodation and registration purposes. Look out for directions in the campus to reach the hospitality desk. Also, you can refer the <a href="http://iitk.ac.in/new/campus-maps">Campus Maps</a>.</p>';

final registrationHTML = '<ul><li><p>Report at the Hospitality desk in Events Ground (behind the New SAC) as soon as you arrive at the campus for accommodation and registration purposes.</p></li><li><p>Every individual has to produce their own original college ID card and a valid Government ID proof at the desk for verification purposes.</p></li><li><p>Furthermore, every individual is advised to carry with him 2 copies of payment receipt (note: payment receipt implies the mail verification of your payment) and 2 copies of your recent passport size photograph as they have to be produced at the Hospitality Desk.</p></li><li><p>Hospitality Team will then provide the accommodation and the Hospitality booklet which will act as your ID card, pass for events, and talk shows on the campus.</p></li><li><p>Registration for WORKSHOPS will be carried out at the Workshops Desk (adjacent to the Hospitality Desk), after which you have to register for accommodation at the Hospitality desk.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Note:</strong> Participants who are attending any workshop are advised to first report at the Workshop Desk and then at the Hospitality desk for accommodation.</p>';